The paper proposes a new model for topic modeling of tagged documents and images, which involves higher-order relations among them. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM). Given that the paper focuses on developing a new model and evaluating its performance in various text and image mining tasks, it is most likely to belong to the machine learning and information retrieval sub-categories. However, the use of images and tags also suggests relevance to computer vision, natural language processing, and multimedia.
